STUDENT.observations: It was an interesting experiment. I think that it may be challenging because sometimes the teacher can contradict his own specifications (at least what you understand about them). But I think it's a good way to see how powerful nonverbal communication can be.

1.comment: The training trial had only one shape, so it was not easy to discover the purpose. When I did it wrong on the first task, teacher returned to the training area and moved the car to the places where the shapes that I was supposed to touch were placed (even if at the training area was nothing in there).

STUDENT.guess: I think I was supposed to touch the squares containing a triangle inside.

TEACHER.observations: It is pretty understandable and usable. I would have spent longer teaching at times but it just would have extended the whole time commitment too much

6.comment: I used my memory of Map #1 to demonstrate which things to touch vs. which to avoid, by touching invisible places in the training map!
